         <abstract>
            <p>The first part of this paper is concerned with global characterizations of both the multivariate $B$-spline and the multivariate truncated power function as smooth piecewise polynomials. In the second part of the paper we establish combinatorial criteria for the linear independence of multivariate $B$-splines corresponding to certain configurations of knot sets.</p>
          </abstract>
